OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Charles
OL,4,CGiles
OL,6,FMr Giles has dementia and his carer
OL,7,Fhelped tell us the story of his D-Day
OL,8,Fexperience with his family's blessing.
OL,10,FCarer Ollie Parker said: "Charles was
OL,11,Fpart of the navigating team so he was
OL,12,Fin charge of getting to the point of
OL,13,Fwhere the action was and stayed in
OL,14,Fline with where the action needed to
OL,15,Fbe.
OL,17,F"It was a destroyer and he was deep in
OL,18,Fthe bowels and that position is well
OL,19,Fwithin the ship itself so he would not
OL,20,Fhave seen a huge amount of the action
OL,21,Foutside the ship.
