OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Charles
OL,4,CGiles
OL,6,F"The thing that stands out that he
OL,7,Falways talked about was the
OL,8,Fcamaraderie and the good times he had
OL,9,Fon the ship. Inside the mess where
OL,10,Fthey had a break from the pain and the
OL,11,Fconflict."
OL,13,FThe night before D-Day the ship
OL,14,Fescorted a convoy to Juno Beach and
OL,15,Ftook part in the bombardment of the
OL,16,Fenemy defence ahead of the beach
OL,17,Flandings.
OL,19,FMr Parker added: "When we took Charles
OL,20,Fto Chatham dockyard to go on a
OL,21,FDestroyer.
